### 🔌 Wiring & Connection Guide (Schema Collegamenti)

Here is exactly how to connect all the components together. Follow these connections step-by-step:

#### 1. Real-Time Clock (DS3231) ➔ ESP32
The RTC handles the time schedule and talks to the ESP32 via I2C protocol:
* **GND** ➔ ESP32 **GND**
* **VCC** ➔ ESP32 **3V3** (or 5V depending on your module version)
* **SDA** ➔ ESP32 **GPIO 21**
* **SCL** ➔ ESP32 **GPIO 22**

#### 2. Dual-Channel Relay Module ➔ ESP32 & Power
The relay module acts as an electronic switch to turn the pumps on and off safely:
* **GND** ➔ ESP32 **GND**
* **IN1** (Controls Pump 1) ➔ ESP32 **GPIO 25**
* **IN2** (Controls Pump 2) ➔ ESP32 **GPIO 26**
* **VCC** ➔ UPS Board **5V Out** (Relays need a stable 5V to click properly)

#### 3. Power Management (UPS Board) ➔ ESP32 & Solar
The UPS board is the heart of the power system, managing the 18650 batteries:
* **5V Output (+ / -)** ➔ Connect to the **5V and GND** pins of the ESP32 to power the microcontroller.
* **Solar Input (+ / -)** ➔ Connect the bare wires coming directly from the **Solar Panel** (Positive to +, Negative to -).

#### 4. Water Pumps & Relay Power Circuit
To power the pumps safely without drawing too much current through the ESP32:
1. Connect the **Negative (-) wire** of both Pump 1 and Pump 2 directly to the **GND** of your UPS power output.
2. Connect a wire from the **5V Positive (+)** of your UPS output to the **COM (Common)** terminal of both relay channels.
3. Connect the **Positive (+) wire of Pump 1** to the **NO (Normally Open)** terminal of Relay Channel 1.
4. Connect the **Positive (+) wire of Pump 2** to the **NO (Normally Open)** terminal of Relay Channel 2.

